Running the dog or human code from function library¶

This runs the dog_or_human code from a custom function library named face_dog.py.

The functions were created in dog_app.ipynb for more details.

Specifically, the functions use OpenCV's implementation of Haar feature-based cascade classifiers to detect human faces, a pre-trained ResNet-50 model to detect dogs in images, and a custom built and trained CNN using transfer learning from InceptionV3 to detect dog breeds. This purposefully only detects faces and dogs. The fact that it doesn't know what cats are isn't a bug, it's a feature :).

make sure you run it in a tensorflow environment. If you followed the tensorflow installation, likely you can switch the the correct environment with: $ source activate tensorflow in the terminal before opening jupyter notbook.
